# Experiment 9: Folder-Level IAM and Policy Inheritance

## Aim
To create a Folder in Google Cloud and assign IAM roles at the folder level to understand policy inheritance across projects.

---

## Step 0: Initial Setup
1. Open Google Cloud Console
2. Ensure you are part of an Organization (required for folders)
3. Select the correct Organization (not just project)

---

## Step 1: Open Resource Manager

1. Navigate to:
   IAM & Admin → Manage Resources

---

## Step 2: Create Folder

1. Click:
   "Create Folder"

2. Enter:
   - Name: test-folder
   - Organization: Select your organization

3. Click:
   "Create"

---

## Step 3: Create Project inside Folder

1. Click:
   "Create Project"

2. Enter:
   - Project Name: test-project
   - Location: test-folder (IMPORTANT)

3. Click:
   "Create"

---

## Step 4: Assign IAM Role at Folder Level

1. Open:
   test-folder

2. Go to:
   Permissions tab

3. Click:
   "Grant Access"

4. Enter:
   - Principal: testuser@gmail.com
   - Role: Viewer

5. Click:
   "Save"

---

## Step 5: Verify Policy Inheritance

1. Navigate to:
   test-project

2. Go to:
   IAM & Admin → IAM

3. Check:
   - testuser@gmail.com is listed
   - Role shows: Viewer
   - Marked as: "Inherited from test-folder"

---

## Observations
- Folder created successfully
- Project created inside the folder
- IAM role assigned at folder level
- Role automatically inherited by the project
- No need to assign role again at project level

---

## Result
Successfully created a folder and assigned IAM roles at the folder level. Verified that roles are inherited by projects within the folder, demonstrating policy inheritance.

---
# 1. Define Variables
export ORG_ID=$(gcloud organizations list --format="value(ID)")
export FOLDER_NAME="test-folder"
export PROJECT_NAME="test-project-$(date +%s)" # Unique ID
export USER_EMAIL="testuser@gmail.com"

# 2. Create the Folder under the Organization
gcloud resource-manager folders create \
    --display-name=$FOLDER_NAME \
    --organization=$ORG_ID

# 3. Get the Folder ID (generated by Google)
export FOLDER_ID=$(gcloud resource-manager folders list \
    --organization=$ORG_ID --filter="display_name:$FOLDER_NAME" \
    --format="value(name)")

# 4. Create a Project inside the Folder
gcloud projects create $PROJECT_NAME \
    --folder=${FOLDER_ID#folders/}

# 5. Assign IAM Role at the Folder Level
gcloud resource-manager folders add-iam-policy-binding ${FOLDER_ID#folders/} \
    --member="user:$USER_EMAIL" \
    --role="roles/viewer"

# 6. Verify Inheritance on the Project
gcloud projects get-iam-policy $PROJECT_NAME \
    --filter="bindings.members:$USER_EMAIL"

